The paper discusses the use of deep learning-based convolutional neural networks to solve the task of inverting the process of producing a 2D x-ray image from a 3D volume. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new dataset and discusses the use of computer simulations, which are relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the application of the approach to real x-rays, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
